# Writer Coordination

- Multiple writer subagents allowed only when writable scopes are explicitly disjoint; never run writers in background.
- Shared files stay parent-owned unless one worker is explicitly assigned sole owner. Shared files: `src/app.module.ts`, `src/main.ts`, `src/shared/**`, `prisma/schema.prisma`, route/permission registries, active `docs/tasks/*.md`, cross-module tests.
- Every writer handoff must list: owned files/dirs, forbidden shared files, expected validation commands.
- Task docs default to single-owner sequence: `planner` creates → `coder` reads → `code-reviewer` updates review status.
- After parallel writers finish, parent must re-read latest content before editing any shared file.
- Overlapping changes attributable to child writers: merge. Unknown source or frozen boundary: stop and ask user.
